description:
When the Eternals are dispatched to investigate strange goings on in Madripoor, they arrive to discover a threat to all of humanity that could render the Horde’s

impending arrival of no consequence! Born of the

Celestials, the Young Gods believe themselves superior to the Eternals. But one question plagues them: why were they created? Left to determine the answer on their own, the Young Gods’ efforts to this end may prove to be the end of all humanity... and only the Eternals stand in their way! Tremble mortals, for the gods are going to war!

Reprints The Eternals #7.
name: True Believers; The Fourth Host

description: We're not in the Marvel Universe anymore, Toto! Being swept up by a whirlwind and dropped off in the strange land of Oz is only the beginning of trouble for Jenny. But she follows the Rainbow Road to find the mighty Wizard and encounters a familiar cast of characters more in need of help than her; a rusty old tin man in need of a heart, a scarecrow whose lost his hammer and maybe his mind, and a shield-toting lion who simply needs to find his courage. And just when they thought things couldn't get any worse, the the Wizard's daughter, the Witch of the West, arrives to utter three ominous words...

Ultimatum hits the Baxter Building! As the team is torn apart in more ways than one, the fate of the Fantastic Four rests on the rocky shoulders of the Thing. Ben Grimm steps up and embarks on a hero’s journey to the very center of the Earth to find the one man who can help his imperiled teammates. And that's just the beginning.
Having discovered the origin of their illness, the Brats attempt to bring down the evil Hive. They get some unexpected help from Ocean's 'invisible' friend Kalu.
Once more unto the Hive! The Brats race to their old home to find a cure for the virus that is killing them one by one! Along the way, they learn a lesson or two about life and responsibility.

volume.name: Bob Marley: Tale of the Tuff Gang

description: origin of some of marvel's finest villains
name: Bring On The Bad Guys

volume.name: Bring on the Bad Guys: Origins of the Marvel Comics Villains

description: It's Marvel Pirate Mania as the Storyteller returns! Gavin is a young man with the ability to reshape the world in his image, but when he crosses paths with Ms. Marvel once more, dark secrets are revealed, and Gavin's life takes a dark turn. Brian Reed (SECRET INVASION: FRONT LINE) and Giuseppe Cammuncoli bring you a tale where anything can happen... and does!
name: Return Of The Storyteller

description: Stormwatch PHD heads to Las Vegas to break in a new sister team. Unfortunately forces that hate them are already there and waiting.
name: What Happens In Vegas

description: Black Betty's secrets revealed.
name: Ladies' Night

description: Jackson King is a man that is known to have many secrets, but not all of them are related to his job. During an interview with a reporter on how he was able to reassemble Stormwatch, many secrets were revealed. Even answers that many fans were asking since the beginning, Why are Fahrenheit, Fuji, Winter, and Hellstrike alive, and how is that possible?

It's just another day at the work for officer Michael Doran, chief of the Post Human Division. Gorgeous seductress, calls from your wife, check on your coworkers and a lot of paperwork to be done. Also, a team of supervillians put your police station under siege, trapping everyone inside.
name: A Day at the Office

description: The Division is a secret US agency working in clandestine operations around the world. It consists on several "special" Agents that possess incredible powers such as telekinesis, clairvoyance, shape shifting, etc. But as every black-op agency, several internal struggles suggests that the Division may not be looking for the greater good. And the questions for Ezra Lowe is, who is the one pulling out the strings in the shadows?
name: The Question

description:
Overview:

In "New Krypton" part 5, the new creative team continues to shake up Supergirl's life as Kryptonian-human relations are strained even further! The turmoil forces Supergirl to make a terrible decision: does she stand with the Kryptonian, the people she's longed to be reunited with, or with the humans, the race she's sworn to protect? On top of that, one of her greatest foes is reactivated with a burning hatred for anyone from Krypton " Rao help us all!
name: New Krypton, Part 5: The Secret Origin of Supergirl

description: When Veronica Gainsburrow died, all hell broke loose. Literally. Now her sexy, undead alter ego is all that stands between the forces of evil and the end of the world. Can she harness her new powers in time to stop this army of darkness? Horror has a Hero—SCARLET VERONICA.
name: New Girl

description: Rachel has befriended Simon, but it takes a strong heart – and a stronger stomach – to follow the peculiar hero on his tour of the netherworld realm known as The In-Between! Sneak a peak behind the curtain and inside a strange world all too familiar to our titular hero.
name: Mousetrap

description: The Skrulls are storming Russia and have not only take War Machine as prisoner, but they have the Winter Guard at the brink of total defeat. But War Machine is not an enemy to take lightly and the Skrulls will have to face him and the wrath of Mother Russia's last defenders: The Winter Guard!
name: War Machine: Weapon of S.H.I.E.L.D. Conclusion

description: The ultimate locked-room murder has been committed. Someone's been killed aboard the international space-station two hundred and twenty miles above the Earth. And now that the killer has at last been revealed, it's going to take more than science to save the rest of the crew -it's going to take a huge leap of faith! A thriller in the vein of Whiteout!

The evil Dr. Combs has reanimated the dead and turned innocent victims into monsters from beyond! Artificially created vampires and werewolves now prowl the streets of Gotham, and only the combined might of The Man of Steel and The Dark Knight can hope to stop them. But when a rogue vampire named Dimeter and a feral werewolf called Janko decide to join their side against Combs and his legion of the undead, Superman and Batman will have to save themselves and all of Gotham from the creatures of the night! Good thing they've called in Green Arrow and his wooden and silver-tipped arrows for help!
name: An Unspeakable Horror!

volume.name: Superman and Batman vs. Vampires and Werewolves

description:
In the dark tradition of Los Angeles noir, The Cleaners is a terrifying new mystery series about a ragtag team of for-hire trauma-scene cleaners led by ex-surgeon Robert Bellarmine. Contracted with sanitizing some of the nastiest crime and accident scenes in the tri-county L.A. basin, the team battles against what could only be described as the grim, unknowable face of the supernatural. But by focusing on the scientific explanation, no matter how aberrant or extraordinary, they counteract centuries-old superstition to prove things are seldom what they seem . . .

In this miniseries, the cleaners crew takes on a series of gruesome tasks starting with a bloodbath that covers an entire neighborhood. This investigation leads them toward uncovering a disturbing mystery involving missing children, which dates back longer than the history of the city itself.
name: Absent Bodies, Part 1 of 4

description: In "Scorched Earth" Part Four, writer Brett Matthews and artist Sergio Cariello are again joined by cover artist John Cassaday as the creative team put the Ranger and Tonto hot on the heels of a serial killer. Plus: Cavendish continues to fall back into old habits as his quest for The Lone Ranger and his revenge continues.
name: Scorched Earth Part 4 of 4

description: The hilarious mini-series concludes as the world threatens to come to an end. The Odd Squad is the only thing standing in the way of imminent destruction - and the fate of the entire planet. It's X-Files by way of Get Smart in this explosively funny series finale written by indie sensation Todd Livingston!

As the superflu known as "Captain Trips" continues to spread across America, the lives of poor souls such as Larry Underwood and Frannie Goldsmith can't help, but be affected by it. And as the media begins to catch wind of rumors about chemical warfare and bubonic plague, the actions of the American government begin to devolve, local and global legal systems start to deteriorate, and two wild and crazy outlaws--Lloyd Henreid and Poke Freeman--decide to take advantage of the situation, wreaking a path of destruction through the American southwest! It's murder and mayhem, Stephen King-style, in the next chapter of the epic struggle between good and evil! Plus, a stunningly visceral regular cover and sketch variant cover from acclaimed artist Lee Bermejo and the third of five connecting variant covers from Perkins – this is a must for any King fan!
name: Captain Trips Part Three

description: Wolverine and Professor X face off against an unholy alliance of enemies old and new, as Sebastian's Shaw's schemes come to fruition. But the greatest danger arises from the most unlikely source, as Xavier's determination to atone for past sins takes him into Daken's scarred and traumatized mind.
name: Original Sin, Part 4

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

name: The Blasphemers: Prelude - Scattering Seeds of Damnation

description: War breaks out within the Nightbreed community. One group wants to live in peace, while the other wants to prey on human flesh. The stakes include the soul of Aaron Boone, now leader of the Nightbreed.
name: The Blasphemers, Part 1 - The Body and Blood

description: A clash between good and evil as the two Nightbreed factions fight to decide whether or not they will feed on the human race. The good guys have severe handicaps thanks to a killer among the police and a treacherous human stalking them, seeking immortality.
name: The Blasphemers, Part 2 - The Sacrament of Meat

description: The flesh-eating Nightbreed strike an unholy deal with a human arms dealer to kill all the Nightbreed who oppose them, especially the Cabal, in a bloody firefight.
name: The Blasphemers, Part 3 - Light Me, a Candle, Said Flesh to the Flame

description: The Cabal is cornered by the flesh-eating creatures that don't want to see him re-unite the Nightbreed. They are allied with an arms dealer who also wants to see the Cabal dead, for reasons of his own.
name: The Blasphemers, Part 4 - The Chicken Coop of the Soul

description: "The Blasphemers" concludes as the Cabal proves his worthiness as the leader of the Nightbreed, and a dinosaur skeleton goes on a rampage through a shopping mall.
name: The Blasphemers, Part 5 - A Sale on Salvation in Aisle 4

description: A South American sight-seeing tour falls victim to a group of the Nightbreed who want to be worshipped as they once were.
name: The Birthing of That Which Was

description: In blood sacrifice to the demon-gods, not even the strong will survive!
name: The Masks of God

description: "THE GENERIC COMIC- Featuring a super hero and a super villain in an exciting story as only A WRITER and A PENCILER could bring it to you. And with AN INKER doing the inking, you know you're in for a treat! (And if that doesn't intrigue you, we don't know what will!) Only from Marvel!" (per solicitation)

name: Healthy Heroes
Safety Heroes

description: Tragedy strikes close to home when Billy and Jimmy are forced to contend with a mysterious and insidious new enemy named Stealth.
name: Double Jeopardy

description: With the dragon from which they draw their power on the loose and tearing a bloody swath through Oligopolis, Billy and Jimmy Lee must risk it all to tame the beast... or die trying.
name: Dragon's Flight

description:
Vesper plunges deep into cyberspace to uncover the truth about the Genetix Past, while the rest of the team fight a rear guard action against a rampaging hoard of Psycho-Warriors.  
 
No one said being a gene-teen was easy!
name: Deadly Harvest Part Two

description: The final battle between Genetix and Tektos.
name: Deadly Harvest Part Six

description: His mission in “Secret Invasion” completed, Deadpool goes back to business as usual, completely unaware that he’s been sold up the river by a villain of incalculable guile -- a villain who won’t soon forget -- or forgive -- Wade’s sins. As the Skrull War winds to its climactic conclusion, the Merc with a Mouth has no idea that the worst for him is yet ahead.
name: Horror Business, Part One: Gross Misconduct

description:
The Sirius Gallery 1997 is a numbered and limited edition collection of new artwork by the alumnus of the mighty Sirius comic book publisher that launched many big names in the comic book creating community.  
 
J.M. Linsner provides a cover for the volume with renditions of dawn, Safety-Belt man and Jatarri for the collection, for the publisher that launched Dawn on public in her first full series Lucifer's Halo.
name: Sirius Gallery

description:
When Ned Flanders accidentally receives a collection of Hans Christian Andersen stories in the mail rather than the Christian fairy tales he expected, Lisa attempts to prevent a literary disaster by sharing the wonderful tales of the Danish storyteller with Rod and Todd.

'The Little Mermaid,' 'Thumbelina,' 'The Ugly Duckling,' and many more classic characters get served up Simpsons-style courtesy of Ian Boothby and Linda Medley (creator of Castle Waiting).
name: Hans Across America

description: "The Death of the Invisible Woman" concludes, with...well, the death of the Invisible Woman!
name: The Galactus Engine

description: In the depths of his heartache over Kitty Pryde, Colossus goes looking for something-- anything-- to stop his pain...and finds a nightmare from the Old Country running rampant in the States. What's their connection? Elsewhere, Angel and the Beast begin a worldwide quest gathering some of the most unique minds on Earth and run across a hero long thought dormant. Emma checks in to a hotel you have to see to believe while poor Scott sits idly by...oh, and then footage showing the Alaskan Massacre that kicked off MESSIAH COMPLEX is released to the media. Just another day in the life of the all new, all different X-MEN!
name: Lovelorn, Part One: Every Little Bit Hurts

description: The Life of Pope John Paul II. The entire story!  From his childhood in Poland to the assassination attempt!
name: The Life of Pope John Paul II

volume.name: The Life of Pope John Paul II

description:
Can Earth survive Lunatik?

Yes, but he is very annoying.

A child that Conan's grandfather saved from death many years ago-now an old man-seeks to return the favor, but can he get to Conan and Caollan before Horsa's warriors capture their Cimmerian prey? And what good is an old man against Aesir soldiers and the vicious witch Olva? Thorgeir the Berserker gets his second round with Conan, and Caollan shows just how tough and wily a Cimmerian woman can be in battle--even when outnumbered. Richard Corben contributes stunning flashback scenes featuring Connacht, Conan's grandfather. In this issue, Corben brings us to a dark, seemingly hopeless time in the older Cimmerian's life, when he was betrayed and enslaved.
name: Cimmeria (Part 5): The Wolf's Promise

description: With Frank Miller's highly anticipated movie adaptation of The Spirit coming in December, DC Comics presents THE SPIRIT SPECIAL, the perfect introduction to Will Eisner's greatest creation! This low-priced special includes four classic stories: 1947's "Sign of the Octopus,"1949's "Black Alley,"and "Sand Saref"and "Bring in Sand Saref,"both from 1950.
name: Sign Of The Octopus;  Black Alley;  Sand Saref;  Bring In Sand Saref

description: A strange child channels the Green Lantern oath and scrawls it on a wall. It's a summons from forces located in another galaxy. A fantastic civilization that has its own Green Lantern requires immediate aid and their only chance for survival rests in the hands of Hal Jordan and the Phantom Stranger!
name: Without Sin: Part One

description:
Overview

A "Batman R.I.P." tie-in! Batgirl literally has her back against the wall as the remaining Outsiders turn against Gotham City’s youngest protector! With Batman out of the picture, Cassandra Cain finds herself suddenly alone. Will the Outsiders ever be the same? The "Batman R.I.P." storyline continues having devastating effects across the DCU!
name: The Network

description: From the pages of TERROR TITANS and the minds of Justin Gray, Jimmy Palmiotti, and Amanda Connor comes a new rock-slinging heroine! As Terra's earth-shaking stunts grab the attention of the world, a new threat rises from beneath the surface. Will Terra live to fight another day, as she takes on the blaze and fury of Pyrite and the Lavarians? And what is the secret behind this new mover and shaker's powers? Guest-starring Power Girl and Doctor Mid-Nite!
name: Who Are You?

description: After Kara's disastrous fight with Maelstrom in Metropolis, Superman takes her on a survival course. They have no powers, poisonous plants and killer animals to contend with and in the meantime, Maelstrom comes face to face with Darkseid.
name: Maelstrom, Part 2

description: The heroic Trinity is long gone and their legacy fades by the minute. But where exactly are Superman, Batman and Wonder Woman – and will they ever return? Don't miss the halfway point in this action-fueled, weekly series exploring the three greatest heroes of all time!
name: Like Ice Melting; Very Different People

description: Discover the secret origin of Ink. The bad-boy of the Young X-Men has been shrouded in mystery, but that ends here, and the truth will shake the team of young mutants.
name: The Y-Men Part 1: Outnumbered

description: Some sins you can never atone for. In the heart of “Secret Invasion,” as the world faces an enormous threat, as every hero in the Marvel Universe is fighting for the very survival of mankind, Frank Castle and Stuart Clarke are trying very, very hard to kill one another. With no more secrets left to be learned and no more places left to hide, these former allies are left with no other choice but to put the other one in the ground. But what about G.W. Bridge? Who's side is he on? And what about all those Skrulls? Who's gonna kill all of them?
name: Secret Invasion, Part 2 of 2

description: The Skrull invasion is finally over and Norman Osborn is the man of the moment... maybe the man of the century! With the whole country at his feet, he decides to play his cards and change the balance of power. While he was in Washington, not only receiving a public ovation but advocating himself as the ideal man to reconstruct the country, in the Thunderbolts Mountains, the now disassembled team will realize that the real enemy was always between them.
name: Burning Down The House, Pt. 1

description: It's girl's day out as Supergirl and Batgirl try to find the perfect location for a tea party. Let's just hope they don't forget about Steaky and Ace!
name: Tea Time

description: Okay, no kidding. This time, for sure, The Spirit gets a break from the hustle and bustle of Central City's mean streets. Maybe fresh air out in the wide, open spaces is just what he needs? Right?
name: (Half) Way Out West

description:
A human scout ship is shot down over the planet Skalorr, a barren rock supporting only two warring life forms, the Terrokors and the Protectons. Both of these races are ancient and have been fighting for hundreds of years. The humans were lucky and encounter the “good guys,” the Protectons. After regrouping in the Protectons’ base, the humans discovered that the two races used to be humanoid before their essences were transformed into the large robotic machines they are now. Tired of staying on the planet, half of the humans rebelled to join the Terrokors. The result is an all-out battle pitting humans and robots against one another with the fate of the planet at stake.

Robotix was a one-shot, toy-inspired title that Marvel released at the height of the Transformers craze.

deck: A group of suburban ninjas must face a demonic threat in New Jersey.
name: Jagged Image
